CHAPTER THREE
THE GEOMANTIC FIGURES
This chapter summarizes the characteristics of each of the sixteen geo-
mantic figures, along with diagrams of their traditional patterns and the
elements with which the patterns correspond. As mentioned already, the
most important feature to note for divination purposes is the elemental
structure ofeach figure, but familiarity with the symbols, images, and ideas
included in the summary will help you in understanding all the dimensions
ofgeomancy.
