Divinatory meaning: Populus in a geomantic chart represents a
gathering or assembly ofpeople, or a large amount ofanything
else. A passive figure that takes on the qualities ofthe figures
that interact with it, Populus tends to be fortunate with fortu-
nate figures and unfortunate with unfortunate ones. Still, it is
usually favorable in matters that benefit from quiet reflection,
and unfavorable in matters demanding focused action.
