figure thus represents change for the better, and is a particu-
larly positive sign for beginnings. Earth, which is both its
inner and outer element, and its elemental structure generally
suggest fertile ground, needing only the energy ofseed and
sunlight; still, much depends on the seed that is planted there.
Divinatory meaning: In a geomantic reading, Caput Draco-
nis represents beginnings and new possibilities. It tends to
vary in meaning with its company, becoming more favorable
with favorable figures and more unfavorable with unfavor-
able ones, but it often foretells a good result with some
difficulty at the beginning. Caput Draconis is favorable in
all matters having to do with beginnings, and unfavorable in
questions where ending something is desirable.
