Commentary: Fortuna Minor is a figure of outer strength
and success, balancing the inner strength of Fortuna Major.
These two figures have the same astrological symbolism but
the opposite elemental structure; they represent the same
kind ofexperience—success—but have sharply different
sources. Fortuna Minor represents success that is brought
about by outside help or circumstances, rather than by the
innate strength symbolized by Fortuna Major. Easily gained,
the success ofFortuna Minor is just as easily lost, and it
produces the best results in situations where rapid change is
expected or desired.These factors are echoed in the sym-
bolism by an unexpected shift in the outer element; Leo is
